WEBVTT

00:01.657 --> 00:03.647
Previously on The Expanse.

00:06.770 --> 00:09.340
<i>Proton molecule... they gave
the goddamn thing a name.</i>

00:09.375 --> 00:11.306
We did not choose this,

00:11.341 --> 00:13.042
but this is our fight now.

00:14.017 --> 00:15.251
<i>We'll hide it.</i>

00:15.285 --> 00:16.485
<i>No one knows we have it.</i>

00:16.519 --> 00:17.686
<i>It'll be safe.</i>

00:17.721 --> 00:19.421
What's happening?

00:19.456 --> 00:21.090
Eros has changed trajectory.

00:21.124 --> 00:23.092
<i>It's now on a direct
collision course with Earth.</i>

00:23.126 --> 00:24.660
<i>♪ </i>

00:24.694 --> 00:26.528
They left me here all alone.

00:26.563 --> 00:28.797
I just want to go home.

00:28.832 --> 00:30.199
<i>Why don't we go to Venus?</i>

00:32.134 --> 00:35.337
<i>The Eros incident was our
first contact with alien life.</i>

00:35.372 --> 00:37.673
It's too dangerous to leave
our sample out there anymore.

00:37.707 --> 00:40.276
We should kill it,
drive it into the goddamn sun.

00:40.310 --> 00:41.310
It's the only way.

00:41.344 --> 00:42.611
It's done?

00:42.646 --> 00:43.846
Yeah, it's done.

00:45.382 --> 00:47.349
They are engaging in orbit!

00:47.384 --> 00:49.285
Free fire, 500 meters!

00:49.319 --> 00:55.491
<i>♪ </i>

00:55.525 --> 00:56.959
[GLASS SHATTERING]

00:56.993 --> 00:58.661
What do you know about
Dr. Lawrence Strickland?

00:58.695 --> 01:00.296
<i>He's my daughter's pediatrician.</i>

01:00.330 --> 01:02.231
<i>You're going to Ganymede
to find Dr. Strickland.</i>

01:02.265 --> 01:03.468
Please take me with you.

01:03.469 --> 01:04.869
You were right about
that thing on Ganymede.

01:04.903 --> 01:06.504
It was a weapons test.

01:06.538 --> 01:08.006
<i>The weapon's up for sale,
and Mars wants it.</i>

01:08.040 --> 01:09.907
What were you doing
with the protomolecule?

01:09.942 --> 01:13.678
<i>We made it... [GASPS] in our own image.</i>

01:13.712 --> 01:16.681
We're not going anywhere
till that thing is dead.

01:16.715 --> 01:18.883
- Got it!
- No, please!

01:18.917 --> 01:19.917
That is not your kid!

01:19.952 --> 01:21.285
<i>Not anymore!</i>

01:21.320 --> 01:23.521
<i>Monsieur Mao, the MCRN "Karakum"</i>

01:23.555 --> 01:24.722
<i>dispatched by Korshunov</i>

01:24.757 --> 01:27.425
<i>to take delivery of your
protomolecule technology</i>

01:27.459 --> 01:29.360
<i>was destroyed over Ganymede.</i>

01:29.395 --> 01:30.728
<i>And I gave the order.</i>

01:30.763 --> 01:33.031
[GUNFIRE]

01:33.065 --> 01:35.366
- Get down!
- [GASPS]

01:35.401 --> 01:37.368
- You're shot.
- Go to the airlock, go.

01:37.403 --> 01:41.639
<i>♪ </i>

01:41.674 --> 01:42.907
Fire!

01:42.941 --> 01:46.077
[GUNFIRE]

01:46.111 --> 01:47.879
[GRUNTS AND GROANS]

01:47.913 --> 01:50.114
<i>The creature gets energy from radiation.</i>

01:50.149 --> 01:51.115
<i>We lure it out.</i>

01:51.150 --> 01:54.385
Prax, it's not Mei!

01:54.420 --> 01:56.721
Firing up the barbecue.

01:56.755 --> 01:59.390
[ENGINE ROARING]

01:59.425 --> 02:02.427
[WHOOSHING]

02:02.461 --> 02:04.462
I think we've stopped.

02:04.496 --> 02:06.097
The protomolecule has changed everything.

02:06.131 --> 02:07.765
I don't ever remember a time

02:07.800 --> 02:10.568
<i>when Earth, Mars, and the Belt
weren't fighting.</i>

02:10.602 --> 02:12.403
<i>No one knows what the protomolecule wants</i>

02:12.438 --> 02:13.571
<i>or what it's doing,</i>

02:13.605 --> 02:15.406
<i>but they are using it anyway.</i>

02:15.441 --> 02:17.008
<i>Earth has it;</i>

02:17.042 --> 02:18.242
<i>Mars has it;</i>

02:18.277 --> 02:19.944
<i>and the Belt needs it too.</i>

02:19.978 --> 02:22.847
Naomi...

02:22.881 --> 02:23.781
what did you do?

02:23.816 --> 02:27.418
I gave the protomolecule to Fred Johnson.

02:30.430 --> 02:33.595
[THUNDER CRASHING]

02:33.596 --> 02:36.164
<i>The Arboghast was above
the Eros impact crater</i>

02:36.198 --> 02:38.066
<i>when the astonishing event occurred.</i>

02:38.100 --> 02:39.567
<i>Experts throughout the system</i>

02:39.602 --> 02:41.369
<i>are now training
their instruments on Venus</i>

02:41.403 --> 02:43.838
<i>to observe the activity
of what multiple sources</i>

02:43.873 --> 02:46.007
<i>are calling "the protomolecule."</i>

02:46.041 --> 02:49.711
<i>[INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER]</i>

02:50.913 --> 02:53.348
<i>In what many believe is a prelude to war.</i>

02:53.382 --> 02:55.617
<i>Planetary defenses
have been placed on high alert</i>

02:55.651 --> 02:58.553
<i>as UNN ships were dispatched
from Earth and Luna</i>

02:58.587 --> 03:01.589
<i>to reinforce fleets
in the Belt and Outer Planets.</i>

03:01.624 --> 03:03.191
<i>After accusing the UN</i>

03:03.225 --> 03:05.426
<i>of assassinating
Defense Minister Korshunov...</i>

03:05.461 --> 03:08.196
<i>And imperialism of Earth
for far too long.</i>

03:08.230 --> 03:10.532
<i>And now their actions
have brought us to the brink.</i>

03:10.566 --> 03:12.534
<i>If they wish to test us in battle,</i>

03:12.568 --> 03:13.902
<i>we are ready.</i>

03:13.936 --> 03:15.537
<i>We will not back down.</i>

03:15.571 --> 03:18.406
<i>Our people are united in purpose.</i>

03:18.440 --> 03:20.275
<i>Mars shall prevail.</i>

03:20.309 --> 03:23.278
<i>[PENSIVE MUSIC]</i>

03:23.312 --> 03:25.713
<i>♪ </i>

03:25.748 --> 03:28.716
<i>[INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER]</i>

03:28.751 --> 03:33.054
<i>♪ </i>

03:33.088 --> 03:34.989
<i>A sense of despair is pregnant.</i>

03:35.024 --> 03:37.392
<i>Most Belters believe that this time,</i>

03:37.426 --> 03:39.160
<i>war is inevitable.</i>

03:39.195 --> 03:42.197
[LASERS ZAPPING, EXPLOSIONS BOOMING]

03:44.166 --> 03:45.900
Third Fleet is on intercept, sir.

03:45.935 --> 03:47.961
Awaiting engagement authorization.

03:48.971 --> 03:50.838
We need to get Mars back to the table

03:50.873 --> 03:53.141
before this madness
spreads past Ganymede.

03:53.175 --> 03:54.442
Where the hell is Chrisjen?

03:54.476 --> 03:55.577
We don't know.

03:55.611 --> 03:56.844
She still hasn't reported in.

03:56.879 --> 03:59.139
Sir, any overtures towards peace,

04:00.549 --> 04:01.816
it would be a grave mistake.

04:01.850 --> 04:03.418
I'm the Secretary General.

04:03.452 --> 04:05.286
I will make that decision.

04:06.453 --> 04:07.647
Of course you will, sir.

04:08.188 --> 04:09.655
We were just sitting across the table,

04:09.690 --> 04:10.890
hammering out a treaty.

04:10.924 --> 04:12.191
It was a Martian smokescreen

04:12.226 --> 04:14.827
to take advantage
of the chaos after Eros.

04:14.862 --> 04:16.896
All the while, they were
redeploying their fleets.

04:16.930 --> 04:18.498
Followed by a wave of lies,

04:18.531 --> 04:21.033
accusing us of assassinating
Defense Minister Korshunov

04:21.067 --> 04:22.401
or firing the first shots over Ganymede.

04:22.436 --> 04:23.710
We don't know who fired
the first shots...

04:23.744 --> 04:25.271
Enough!

04:25.305 --> 04:27.740
Mars has bloviated for a century

04:27.774 --> 04:29.709
about creating a paradise for its people.

04:29.743 --> 04:31.344
And what have they built instead?

04:31.378 --> 04:36.182
A society serving a single purpose: war.

04:36.216 --> 04:40.386
Sir, every conflict assessment
concludes the same thing.

04:40.420 --> 04:41.687
They have better ships,

04:41.722 --> 04:43.456
but we have significantly more.

04:43.490 --> 04:45.291
In an all-out war, we prevail.

04:45.325 --> 04:46.325
All-out war?

04:46.360 --> 04:48.761
If Mars gets a hold
of whatever's on Venus,

04:48.795 --> 04:50.029
this alien technology,

04:50.063 --> 04:51.631
I believe Earth is over.

04:51.665 --> 04:53.366
This is happening on my watch.

04:53.400 --> 04:54.901
I get to wear this, not you.

04:54.935 --> 04:57.603
Sir, in five years,
Mars will have the strength

04:57.638 --> 04:59.372
to impose their will on the system,

04:59.406 --> 05:01.374
to shut Earth off
from the resources of the Belt.

05:01.408 --> 05:04.413
I mean, at that point,
we may as well be their colony.

05:06.000 --> 05:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

05:17.257 --> 05:20.493
Future generations
will look back on this day

05:20.527 --> 05:24.130
as the moment that
you forged your legacy.

05:27.668 --> 05:29.688
Convene the Security Council.

05:30.771 --> 05:33.072
I want a formal declaration of war.

05:33.106 --> 05:35.741
<i>[FOREBODING MUSIC]</i>

05:35.776 --> 05:37.577
You heard the Secretary General.

05:37.611 --> 05:38.945
Let's go.

05:38.979 --> 05:40.479
Get this clear, people.

05:40.514 --> 05:42.582
I need five scenarios,
including exit strategies.

05:42.616 --> 05:44.417
Joe, go with her.

05:44.451 --> 05:46.419
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

05:46.453 --> 05:52.291
<i>♪ </i>

05:54.127 --> 05:57.296
[CRACKLING AND ELECTRONIC BEEP]

05:57.998 --> 06:01.367
[BOOTS CLANKING]

06:01.401 --> 06:04.470
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

06:05.639 --> 06:07.607
<i>Reactor shielding's intact.</i>

06:07.641 --> 06:09.809
<i>Nothing critical damaged.</i>

06:11.545 --> 06:12.845
[CRACKLING]

06:12.879 --> 06:16.282
[FLAME WHOOSHING]

06:19.886 --> 06:23.489
[SIZZLING AND CRACKLING]

06:24.891 --> 06:26.492
Boys...

06:30.063 --> 06:33.165
There any more residual
protomolecule back there?

06:33.200 --> 06:35.067
<i>No, I think we're square.</i>

06:35.102 --> 06:36.963
<i>All right, head in.</i>

06:39.506 --> 06:40.840
[ELECTRONIC BEEP]

06:40.874 --> 06:43.409
[WELDER CRACKLING]

06:43.443 --> 06:46.412
<i>[EERIE MUSIC]</i>

06:46.446 --> 06:51.517
<i>♪ </i>

06:51.551 --> 06:54.520
<i>[FOREBODING MUSIC]</i>

06:54.554 --> 06:58.824
<i>♪ </i>

06:58.859 --> 06:59.892
<i>Prax...</i>

06:59.926 --> 07:01.327
<i>♪ </i>

07:01.361 --> 07:02.395
<i>Prax,</i>

07:02.429 --> 07:05.331
<i>you got the cargo bay sealed up yet?</i>

07:05.365 --> 07:07.867
Yeah, I was... just finishing up.

07:07.901 --> 07:10.202
<i>[SOMBER MUSIC]</i>

07:12.372 --> 07:13.406
Amos.

07:13.440 --> 07:14.540
Look, I know Holden,

07:14.574 --> 07:15.875
and there's no way he's okay

07:15.909 --> 07:17.076
after everything that went down.

07:17.110 --> 07:18.338
What do we do?

07:20.113 --> 07:22.148
We leave him the hell alone.

07:23.884 --> 07:24.917
Amos, listen to me...

07:24.951 --> 07:26.752
Hey, you like Ceres, right?

07:26.787 --> 07:28.888
There's probably a lot
of great dock work on there,

07:28.922 --> 07:30.289
and we know they got good brothels.

07:30.324 --> 07:31.691
What the hell you going on about?

07:31.725 --> 07:33.157
Our family is falling apart.

07:33.191 --> 07:34.944
- Do you understand that?
- We were never a family, Alex.

07:34.978 --> 07:37.530
All we did was draw
lucky straws on the Cant.

07:37.564 --> 07:39.565
We were stronger together; now we're not.

07:39.599 --> 07:41.233
[GRUNTS]

07:41.268 --> 07:43.269
So that's your answer?
We just let everything go?

07:43.303 --> 07:44.870
After everything we've been through,

07:44.905 --> 07:46.372
our ship, our home,
you want to lose the "Roci"?

07:46.406 --> 07:48.407
You mean the ship
that we stole from Mars?

07:48.442 --> 07:50.209
We're the only ones who can fix this.

07:50.243 --> 07:52.445
You keep telling yourself that.

07:57.317 --> 07:59.796
No, we're not done here.

08:00.654 --> 08:03.155
Look, just look in my eyes and
tell me the God's honest truth.

08:03.190 --> 08:04.457
What were you thinking

08:04.491 --> 08:06.926
when Naomi told you what she did?

08:06.960 --> 08:09.161
I'm not gonna lie, I didn't
know what she was saying,

08:09.196 --> 08:11.731
'cause my blood was so hot in my ears.

08:11.765 --> 08:14.100
<i>[PENSIVE MUSIC]</i>

08:14.134 --> 08:16.669
She's not the person I thought she was.

08:16.703 --> 08:23.542
<i>♪ </i>

08:26.380 --> 08:28.114
<i>Guys, check your alerts.</i>

08:28.148 --> 08:31.417
[ELECTRONIC BEEPING]

08:34.955 --> 08:36.422
[ELECTRONIC BEEP]

08:36.456 --> 08:39.001
We're about to be
in the middle of a war zone.

08:40.159 --> 08:41.693
We'll need a new transponder name

08:41.727 --> 08:43.629
and drive signature.

08:45.065 --> 08:47.433
This ship would be a prize
for either side.

08:47.467 --> 08:49.135
<i>Copy that.</i>

08:49.169 --> 08:51.137
<i>♪ </i>

08:51.171 --> 08:54.140
[CRACKLING]

08:54.174 --> 08:57.143
<i>[ROUSING INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC]</i>

08:57.177 --> 09:04.450
<i>♪ </i>

10:06.844 --> 10:14.877
Synced & corrected by -robtor-
www.addic7ed.com

10:15.927 --> 10:18.895
<i>[FOREBODING MUSIC]</i>

10:18.930 --> 10:24.067
<i>♪ </i>

10:24.102 --> 10:26.169
- [GROANING]
- It's okay.

10:26.204 --> 10:28.638
- Stay with me now.
- [GROWLS]

10:28.673 --> 10:29.906
Stay with me.

10:29.941 --> 10:31.641
- It's okay.
- [ELECTRONIC BEEPING]

10:31.676 --> 10:33.910
- It's okay.
- [BOOTS THUDDING]

10:33.945 --> 10:36.446
We still have hostiles on board.

10:36.481 --> 10:38.782
They've killed the elevator,
which is our only way out.

10:38.816 --> 10:40.283
So first things first.

10:40.318 --> 10:42.085
I'm gonna leave the room
for five minutes.

10:42.120 --> 10:43.787
You can hold the fort that long.

10:43.821 --> 10:46.490
I brought you so you could
hold the fucking fort, not me.

10:46.524 --> 10:47.924
[STRAINED] Go, Bobbie, get out of here.

10:47.959 --> 10:50.627
- Shut up.
- [GROANS]

10:50.661 --> 10:51.628
Pick it up.

10:51.662 --> 10:52.629
I don't want to.

10:52.663 --> 10:54.231
Pick it up!

10:55.566 --> 10:57.801
If anyone else but me
comes through that door,

10:57.835 --> 10:59.169
you put them on the ground.

10:59.203 --> 11:01.478
Don't you dare leave us here.

11:02.473 --> 11:03.640
[GROANS]

11:05.743 --> 11:09.446
<i>[DRAMATIC MUSIC]</i>

11:09.480 --> 11:11.681
[METAL SCRAPING]

11:11.716 --> 11:14.317
<i>♪ </i>

11:14.352 --> 11:16.186
I'll be right back.

11:17.722 --> 11:19.489
You're fired!

11:21.492 --> 11:22.492
[HEAVY THUD]

11:22.527 --> 11:26.997
<i>♪ </i>

11:28.232 --> 11:30.634
[DOOR CLANGS]

11:30.668 --> 11:31.835
I thought we had a deal.

11:31.869 --> 11:33.036
New deal.

11:33.070 --> 11:34.371
I was rooting for you.

11:34.405 --> 11:35.906
Oh, it's what kept me going.

11:35.940 --> 11:38.008
I need you to help me
take control of the ship.

11:38.042 --> 11:40.210
I'm just a junior electrician.

11:40.244 --> 11:42.546
Well, today you get to be a hero.

11:42.548 --> 11:45.482
(CLACKING)

11:57.777 --> 12:01.046
[FOOTSTEPS THUDDING]

12:02.715 --> 12:06.584
Cargo bay is sealed and pressurized.

12:10.156 --> 12:11.857
Inners finally got their war.

12:11.891 --> 12:13.892
I need a new name for our transponder.

12:15.561 --> 12:16.628
From me?

12:16.663 --> 12:18.012
Why not?

12:18.898 --> 12:21.166
Okay, how about, um...

12:22.302 --> 12:23.902
Hmm.

12:24.904 --> 12:26.038
How about "Contorta"?

12:26.072 --> 12:28.974
It's short for <i>Pinus Contorta</i>
<i>or </i><i>P. Contorta.</i>

12:29.008 --> 12:30.909
It's this type of pine tree from Earth,

12:30.943 --> 12:33.378
does surprisingly well in low-G.

12:33.413 --> 12:35.547
Spent a lot of time with them
for my dissertation.

12:35.581 --> 12:36.948
They're good company.

12:36.983 --> 12:38.950
Actually quite fascinating.

12:39.519 --> 12:43.538
In order for them to survive,
they have to die with fire.

12:46.092 --> 12:48.460
The seeds come out of the fire.

12:52.665 --> 12:54.900
C-O-N-T-O-R-T-A.

12:54.934 --> 12:57.769
[ELECTRONIC BEEPING]

12:57.804 --> 13:00.405
[CHUCKLES]
That's the wisdom of the pines.

13:00.440 --> 13:03.408
<i>[PENSIVE MUSIC]</i>

13:03.443 --> 13:10.449
<i>♪ </i>

13:14.721 --> 13:17.522
[ENGINE ROARING]

13:17.557 --> 13:19.658
<i>I could say you owe me</i>

13:19.692 --> 13:22.127
or that we have a debt to settle,

13:22.161 --> 13:24.996
but that would be playing
yesterday's game.

13:25.031 --> 13:27.540
And there's no longer time for that,

13:28.134 --> 13:30.435
because now the Belt is in a position

13:30.470 --> 13:32.471
to become an equal player,

13:32.505 --> 13:35.273
because I have the Inners' weapon,

13:35.308 --> 13:37.884
and you have the key
to harnessing that weapon.

13:38.511 --> 13:40.178
The more you share,

13:40.213 --> 13:43.148
the more your bowl will be plentiful.

13:47.687 --> 13:54.960
<i>♪ </i>

13:57.563 --> 13:59.164
[ELECTRONIC BEEP]

14:10.676 --> 14:12.644
[ELECTRONIC BEEPING]

14:12.678 --> 14:16.214
[GROANING]

14:16.249 --> 14:18.049
Why are you looking at me like that?

14:18.084 --> 14:19.151
I saved your life.

14:19.185 --> 14:20.519
I have a new dent in my skull.

14:20.553 --> 14:23.355
- Would you like another one?
- [SIGHS]

14:23.389 --> 14:25.924
[GROWLS AND GROANS]

14:25.958 --> 14:28.129
Where's our Martian tank?

14:28.163 --> 14:30.162
[GROANS]

14:30.196 --> 14:31.830
So you're in charge of defense?

14:31.864 --> 14:33.331
Damn right.

14:33.366 --> 14:36.435
Well, it suits you. [GROANS]

14:36.469 --> 14:39.604
Errinwright gave the order to kill you.

14:39.639 --> 14:40.906
He'll want confirmation,

14:40.940 --> 14:43.175
which he won't get from that guy.

14:43.209 --> 14:45.010
So what's Errinwright's next move?

14:45.044 --> 14:47.012
He's got people on that escort ship.

14:47.046 --> 14:49.080
We have to assume they'll be back.

14:49.115 --> 14:50.549
So we'll take control of this boat,

14:50.583 --> 14:51.850
haul ass to that safe port,

14:51.884 --> 14:53.351
where we can broadcast out for help.

14:53.386 --> 14:55.722
Unless you have a better bad idea.

14:55.756 --> 14:57.338
No.

14:58.124 --> 15:00.125
- All right, I'm ready.
- Wait.

15:00.159 --> 15:02.027
- Let's do this.
- Let me help you.

15:02.061 --> 15:03.728
- [GROANS]
- Hold on... what?

15:03.763 --> 15:06.298
Maybe I'll just... [GRUNTS]

15:06.332 --> 15:07.466
For a minute.

15:07.500 --> 15:08.700
[WHOOSHING]

15:08.734 --> 15:10.702
Shit.

15:10.736 --> 15:12.804
[GUNFIRE]

15:12.839 --> 15:15.106
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

15:15.821 --> 15:17.322
Well done, Madam.

15:19.579 --> 15:20.579
This is Theo.

15:20.613 --> 15:21.880
He's gonna help us out.

15:21.914 --> 15:22.881
Give me that.

15:22.915 --> 15:24.359
- Huh?
- Yeah.

15:24.394 --> 15:25.420
Fleet reports, sir.

15:25.421 --> 15:26.621
Leave them with the office.

15:26.656 --> 15:28.023
I have a draft of an official statement

15:28.057 --> 15:29.524
for you to review, sir.

15:29.558 --> 15:31.559
Keep me apprised
of any additional changes.

15:31.594 --> 15:33.194
Yes, sir.

15:33.229 --> 15:34.667
Privacy.

15:35.898 --> 15:37.879
Have you heard from Avasarala?

15:38.734 --> 15:40.969
No, you?

15:41.003 --> 15:43.605
- No.
- [DOOR RATTLES CLOSED]

15:43.639 --> 15:45.140
[SIGHS]

15:45.174 --> 15:46.541
Mm.

15:46.575 --> 15:48.476
She knows.

15:48.511 --> 15:50.933
What the hell you talking about, Sadavir?

15:52.181 --> 15:53.984
Sir, we need to discuss Eros.

15:54.018 --> 15:54.964
Right now?

15:54.998 --> 15:56.051
I haven't been forthright

15:56.085 --> 15:57.385
about Avasarala's absence

15:57.420 --> 15:58.653
or her recent actions,

15:58.688 --> 15:59.954
not while there was still any doubt.

15:59.989 --> 16:01.423
Doubt about what?

16:04.360 --> 16:05.660
I believe she's involved

16:05.695 --> 16:07.729
in a conspiracy against this government.

16:07.763 --> 16:09.064
You'd better be goddamn sure

16:09.098 --> 16:11.621
before bringing charges like that to me.

16:12.668 --> 16:14.002
For several years,

16:14.036 --> 16:16.104
Chrisjen has been running
a shadow government.

16:17.173 --> 16:18.306
[SIGHS]

16:18.341 --> 16:19.379
Her public attacks

16:19.413 --> 16:21.109
against Jules-Pierre Mao and Fred Johnson

16:21.143 --> 16:24.245
were calculated to cover up
the truth about Eros,

16:24.280 --> 16:27.949
that it was a weapons test
of the alien technology.

16:27.983 --> 16:29.484
She saved Earth from Eros.

16:29.518 --> 16:32.787
From a disaster
that she unleashed herself.

16:32.822 --> 16:35.156
Look, it was Chrisjen who convinced us

16:35.191 --> 16:37.092
to give control of the missiles
to Fred Johnson

16:37.126 --> 16:38.626
during the Eros crisis...

16:38.661 --> 16:40.428
missiles that still go unaccounted for.

16:40.463 --> 16:41.463
So where is she now?

16:41.497 --> 16:42.530
According to my sources,

16:42.565 --> 16:44.165
she's left for a covert meeting

16:44.200 --> 16:46.301
on board a ship
owned by Jules-Pierre Mao,

16:46.335 --> 16:48.036
accompanied by the Martian defector.

16:48.070 --> 16:51.306
And that ship is currently
running dark in the Belt.

16:53.142 --> 16:56.144
Why the hell wouldn't you
tell me about this, Sadavir?

16:58.848 --> 17:00.962
Because this is a woman I love.

17:02.017 --> 17:03.985
Christ, she's almost a mother to me.

17:06.155 --> 17:08.957
If our relationship
has blinded my judgment,

17:08.991 --> 17:10.858
I'll answer for that.

17:13.496 --> 17:15.195
Do you think

17:15.231 --> 17:18.867
that she would offer
the protomolecule to Mars?

17:18.901 --> 17:20.300
Anything's possible

17:20.336 --> 17:23.003
when she realizes she's no longer safe.

17:29.678 --> 17:31.513
What do you want me to do?

17:35.684 --> 17:37.552
Apprehend her,

17:37.586 --> 17:39.521
at all costs.

17:48.646 --> 17:50.714
<i>[WOMAN SPEAKING IN
FOREIGN LANGUAGE ON RADIO]</i>

17:50.749 --> 17:53.055
[GRUNTING LOUDLY]

17:59.887 --> 18:01.721
[ELECTRONIC BEEP]

18:01.755 --> 18:03.790
[SIGHS AND GRUNTS]

18:10.864 --> 18:12.899
They had a sample all along.

18:12.933 --> 18:14.167
Holden lied to us.

18:14.201 --> 18:16.436
Who told you where to find it?

18:16.470 --> 18:17.737
Naomi Nagata.

18:17.771 --> 18:19.505
Hmm.

18:19.540 --> 18:22.508
- Bitch.
- Now we have a deterrent.

18:22.543 --> 18:23.843
And that means power.

18:23.877 --> 18:26.012
And how long before Anderson Dawes

18:26.046 --> 18:27.714
steals this from you too?

18:27.748 --> 18:29.048
Oh, no, he's not gonna steal it,

18:29.083 --> 18:31.484
because I already told him.

18:31.485 --> 18:33.452
Look, he has the scientist

18:33.487 --> 18:36.155
who's the key to opening this lock.

18:36.189 --> 18:37.323
You told him?

18:37.357 --> 18:40.893
New day, new bedfellows.

18:40.927 --> 18:44.163
We can't afford
to be shortsighted right now.

18:47.768 --> 18:51.003
You're crawling into bed
with Anderson Dawes...

18:52.773 --> 18:54.807
Who incited my Belters

18:54.841 --> 18:57.536
into nearly firing missiles at Earth...

18:58.579 --> 19:03.215
who nearly destroyed Tycho
and got both of us killed.

19:08.955 --> 19:12.024
[DOOR CLICKS OPEN AND SHUT]

19:16.730 --> 19:21.033
[METALLIC GRINDING]

19:23.870 --> 19:25.871
Transponder's done.

19:27.274 --> 19:28.741
Masking our transponder

19:28.775 --> 19:31.544
isn't gonna keep us alive for very long.

19:33.213 --> 19:35.047
We should go to Tycho!

19:39.419 --> 19:40.719
No.

19:40.754 --> 19:42.188
Fred Johnson will help us.

19:42.222 --> 19:43.589
Of course he will.

19:43.623 --> 19:45.090
You brought him the blue goo.

19:45.125 --> 19:47.693
Now you want to bring him
a nice little warship.

19:47.727 --> 19:49.295
What the hell were you thinking, Naomi?

19:49.329 --> 19:51.530
Do you have any idea how many
more people are gonna die

19:51.565 --> 19:52.731
because of what you did?

19:52.766 --> 19:54.200
Fewer Belters...

19:54.234 --> 19:55.768
Are you kidding me?

19:55.802 --> 19:58.370
You know, I wanted to give
that shit to Mars, remember?

19:58.405 --> 20:00.606
But we all decided as a group

20:00.640 --> 20:01.974
to fly that crap into the sun.

20:02.008 --> 20:03.542
So what gives you the right

20:03.577 --> 20:04.777
to make that decision for all of us?

20:04.811 --> 20:06.712
We were talking about survival.

20:06.746 --> 20:09.915
Tycho is how we survive.

20:09.950 --> 20:12.051
We're not going to Tycho.

20:12.085 --> 20:14.320
We'll take our chances
on Pallas or Ceres.

20:14.354 --> 20:16.889
There's plenty of places
to hole up and ride this out.

20:16.923 --> 20:18.557
Everyone knows who we are,

20:18.592 --> 20:20.559
and a lot of them consider us criminals.

20:20.594 --> 20:22.261
Five minutes after we dock,

20:22.295 --> 20:24.730
they'll rat us out to Mars
for a nice little finder's fee.

20:24.764 --> 20:26.232
And if it's a Martian patrol,

20:26.266 --> 20:28.000
they will take back this ship by force.

20:28.034 --> 20:31.003
And if it's an Earth patrol,
they'll just blow us up.

20:31.037 --> 20:33.405
We've got no friends, no safe harbor.

20:33.440 --> 20:34.907
We are living on borrowed time

20:34.941 --> 20:37.943
if we don't get this ship parked.

20:41.448 --> 20:42.848
Get us to Tycho,

20:42.883 --> 20:45.951
and you'll never
have to see my face again.

20:53.026 --> 20:55.461
Come on, let's finish this up.

20:55.495 --> 20:57.396
All right, bring it in.

21:06.640 --> 21:08.607
[METAL CLANKING]

21:08.642 --> 21:11.610
<i>[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]</i>

21:11.645 --> 21:14.179
<i>♪ </i>

21:23.423 --> 21:26.191
[COUGHS AND GROANS]

21:29.162 --> 21:30.496
Get behind me.

21:30.530 --> 21:32.364
This is gonna get ugly.

21:32.399 --> 21:36.201
<i>[TENSE MUSIC]</i>

21:36.236 --> 21:37.202
Don't shoot.

21:37.237 --> 21:38.304
We're unarmed.

21:38.338 --> 21:39.505
We're just a flight crew.

21:39.539 --> 21:42.341
<i>♪ </i>

21:42.375 --> 21:45.044
- [ELECTRICITY CRACKLING]
- [YELLING]

21:46.613 --> 21:47.980
<i>[DRAMATIC MUSIC]</i>

21:48.014 --> 21:50.149
[GUNFIRE]

21:50.183 --> 21:53.319
[PANTING]

21:54.081 --> 21:55.888
I tweaked the engines
to burn hot and dirty.

21:55.922 --> 21:57.323
As long as no one gets too close,

21:57.357 --> 21:59.325
we'll just look like
another shitty freighter.

21:59.359 --> 22:01.594
When you're done, have Alex
power down the comms array

22:01.628 --> 22:02.661
for silent running.

22:02.696 --> 22:04.029
Roger that.

22:05.532 --> 22:07.032
We should go to Tycho.

22:10.370 --> 22:12.148
Alex thinks so too.

22:12.706 --> 22:15.207
I hate it, but she's right.

22:15.241 --> 22:16.241
Tycho?

22:16.276 --> 22:18.510
It's the only way
to keep the crew breathing

22:18.545 --> 22:20.112
and out of a Martian gulag.

22:20.146 --> 22:21.847
Fred Johnson's the devil we know.

22:21.881 --> 22:25.117
And he owes us, because of Naomi.

22:25.151 --> 22:26.719
Yep.

22:28.989 --> 22:31.991
Let me know when everything's finished.

22:42.502 --> 22:43.929
How's your leg?

22:44.604 --> 22:46.538
It's fine.

22:46.573 --> 22:47.718
Is it?

22:47.752 --> 22:50.442
Because you seem like you're
in a lot of pain, and I just...

22:50.477 --> 22:51.810
I'm good.

22:51.845 --> 22:53.245
I'm good.

22:55.582 --> 22:57.349
Okay.

23:05.792 --> 23:07.726
[INHALES SHARPLY]

23:07.761 --> 23:09.328
[EXHALES]

23:09.362 --> 23:11.563
[ELECTRONIC BEEP, WHOOSH, CLICKING]

23:11.598 --> 23:12.898
[ELECTRONIC BEEPING]

23:12.932 --> 23:14.566
[ELECTRONIC BEEP, WHOOSH, CLICKING]

23:14.601 --> 23:15.768
[ELECTRONIC BEEPING]

23:15.802 --> 23:16.935
[BANG]

23:16.970 --> 23:19.405
[ELECTRONIC BEEPING]

23:25.612 --> 23:26.679
[GROANS]

23:26.713 --> 23:29.615
[BANGING AND CLATTERING]

23:29.649 --> 23:32.918
[PANTING]

23:35.722 --> 23:38.057
You should try tea.

23:38.841 --> 23:41.543
<i>[DRAMATIC MUSIC]</i>

23:41.577 --> 23:45.213
<i>♪ </i>

23:49.734 --> 23:52.636
Hey, are you okay?

23:52.670 --> 23:54.571
Feels like a hangover.

23:54.605 --> 23:56.406
Yeah, you'll be okay.

23:56.441 --> 23:59.142
[GROANING]

23:59.177 --> 24:01.078
I always wanted to fly this thing.

24:01.112 --> 24:02.446
They tell you, get your training,

24:02.480 --> 24:03.547
get certified,

24:03.581 --> 24:05.382
and then they never let you
near the control room.

24:05.416 --> 24:07.050
It's a total who-you-know type deal,

24:07.085 --> 24:09.319
- this whole company.
- [ALARM BLARES]

24:09.353 --> 24:11.054
What was that?

24:11.089 --> 24:12.222
What the hell are you doing?

24:12.256 --> 24:13.724
That wasn't me.

24:13.758 --> 24:14.891
It's the automatic defense
countermeasures.

24:14.926 --> 24:16.993
Defense against what?

24:17.028 --> 24:18.462
Errinwright is going with missiles

24:18.496 --> 24:19.730
from that escort ship.

24:19.764 --> 24:21.264
That would have been my move too.

24:21.299 --> 24:23.400
Missiles?

24:23.434 --> 24:24.935
17 minutes till impact

24:24.969 --> 24:27.571
if this perfume bottle
maintains current thrust.

24:27.605 --> 24:29.005
Shit, wait.

24:29.040 --> 24:30.741
When I was not selling out
to the captain,

24:30.775 --> 24:32.342
he told us Mao kept his kid's ship

24:32.376 --> 24:33.577
up in the hangar bay...

24:33.611 --> 24:34.978
a racing ship.

24:35.012 --> 24:36.780
Let's go, move.

24:39.117 --> 24:41.418
All communications
come through here, yes?

24:41.452 --> 24:43.920
A record of every message
in and out of the ship?

24:43.955 --> 24:45.856
There's a comms buffer
somewhere in the memory panels.

24:45.890 --> 24:48.425
- Get it for me, please.
- Now?

24:48.459 --> 24:49.860
Is this our priority?

24:49.894 --> 24:51.928
Errinwright's message should be on there,

24:51.963 --> 24:54.364
the one that proves he's
a treasonous piece of shit

24:54.398 --> 24:55.966
whose balls should be ground into...

24:56.000 --> 24:57.300
It proves nothing if we're space junk.

24:57.335 --> 24:58.935
There are dozens
of modules in that system.

24:58.970 --> 24:59.970
It would take me hours.

25:00.004 --> 25:01.271
Then stop wasting time.

25:01.305 --> 25:02.706
It's my job to keep you alive,

25:02.740 --> 25:03.874
and you're making it damn difficult.

25:03.908 --> 25:05.142
If I don't have any evidence,

25:05.176 --> 25:07.110
then my life isn't worth much either.

25:07.145 --> 25:08.311
Should I just pick her up?

25:08.346 --> 25:09.312
You try it.

25:09.347 --> 25:10.313
There's no time.

25:10.348 --> 25:11.448
Hey, hey, hey.

25:11.482 --> 25:12.716
You, you're scared.

25:12.750 --> 25:14.284
You're overwhelmed.

25:14.318 --> 25:15.786
And so are we.

25:15.820 --> 25:16.820
Take a breath.

25:16.854 --> 25:18.121
[BOTH INHALE AND EXHALE]

25:18.156 --> 25:20.323
You have a family
you want to get back to,

25:20.358 --> 25:21.625
someone you love.

25:21.659 --> 25:22.859
We're the same.

25:22.894 --> 25:26.496
Now focus and get me what I need.

25:26.531 --> 25:28.498
It is very important.

25:29.500 --> 25:31.234
The ship is pretty tense.

25:31.269 --> 25:32.969
You could have mentioned that on Tycho.

25:33.004 --> 25:35.906
Some things are in flux right now.

25:35.940 --> 25:37.974
Nature's only constant... change.

25:38.009 --> 25:39.810
[CHUCKLES LIGHTLY]

25:39.844 --> 25:42.279
You really like botany metaphors.

25:43.881 --> 25:45.248
How about one for a guy

25:45.283 --> 25:48.151
who has a problem tilting at windmills?

25:48.186 --> 25:49.586
Tilting at windmills?

25:49.620 --> 25:52.122
I tend to take on fights
that can't be won.

25:53.224 --> 25:54.991
It's nice to let go of all of that.

25:55.026 --> 25:56.326
It's too bad.

25:56.360 --> 25:57.861
It's the way a child looks at things,

25:57.895 --> 26:00.063
with a sense of the possible.

26:02.700 --> 26:07.070
A child who won't grow up
turns into a fool.

26:07.104 --> 26:08.505
But fools keep going,

26:08.539 --> 26:11.541
even when they know
there's no chance of winning.

26:14.312 --> 26:16.546
I knew a guy like that once.

26:18.482 --> 26:20.050
What happened to him?

26:25.323 --> 26:27.524
That wasn't Mei on our ship.

26:30.228 --> 26:33.029
There was nothing human in those eyes.

26:35.733 --> 26:37.567
I'll probably never know.

26:42.240 --> 26:44.574
I got to learn to live with that...

26:48.079 --> 26:49.913
Not knowing.

26:51.415 --> 26:54.384
<i>[PENSIVE MUSIC]</i>

26:54.418 --> 26:59.155
<i>♪ </i>

26:59.190 --> 27:01.091
- [ALARM BLARING]
- [GRUNTS]

27:01.125 --> 27:04.127
I got it. I got it.

27:06.030 --> 27:07.998
You've done your planet a great service.

27:08.032 --> 27:09.399
She says that to everyone.

27:09.433 --> 27:10.834
Let's go.

27:10.868 --> 27:12.469
[GROANS]

27:12.503 --> 27:16.473
<i>[DRAMATIC MUSIC]</i>

27:16.507 --> 27:17.641
Clear.

27:25.016 --> 27:27.417
That's a Series-6.

27:27.451 --> 27:29.286
- A two-seater.
- Fuck!

27:29.320 --> 27:33.256
There's got to be a way
we can all fit in there.

27:33.291 --> 27:34.524
Pilot and navigator.

27:34.558 --> 27:36.159
Anyone not strapped in is hamburger

27:36.193 --> 27:37.928
at the speeds that ship will be moving.

27:37.962 --> 27:39.262
I'm certified. I can fly it.

27:39.297 --> 27:40.630
You're coming with me to the drop ship.

27:40.665 --> 27:43.433
Bobbie, you'll fly Avasarala out of here,

27:43.467 --> 27:45.936
somewhere you can broadcast out for help.

27:45.970 --> 27:47.270
You can pilot, right?

27:47.305 --> 27:49.005
- Well enough.
- Does that mean yes?

27:49.040 --> 27:50.507
That means I'll handle it.

27:50.541 --> 27:52.509
Hey, I checked the flight deck
when I got my armor.

27:52.543 --> 27:54.110
They've shot the pilot
and trashed the controls.

27:54.145 --> 27:55.478
We'll manage.

27:55.513 --> 27:57.113
I'm not getting into that fucking coffin!

27:57.148 --> 27:58.448
Yeah, but you are.

27:58.482 --> 28:00.116
- The hangar bay won't open.
- What?

28:00.151 --> 28:01.217
It's the countermeasures.

28:01.252 --> 28:02.319
When the ship's under threat,

28:02.353 --> 28:04.120
everything goes into lockdown.

28:04.155 --> 28:05.655
Find us another way.

28:05.690 --> 28:06.957
I'm sorry.

28:06.991 --> 28:09.092
At full burn, the bay will never open.

28:11.162 --> 28:12.996
Stay here.

28:19.491 --> 28:22.574
♪

28:22.574 --> 28:24.108
- All right.
- [SIGHS]

28:24.142 --> 28:27.378
Let's... put you to sleep.

28:31.850 --> 28:33.551
Record message.

28:34.653 --> 28:39.156
Uh, from Alex Kamal
to Talissa and Melas Kamal,

28:39.191 --> 28:44.962
Residential Dome 2-6,
Breach Candy District.

28:47.252 --> 28:48.786
[ELECTRONIC BEEP]

28:50.969 --> 28:52.469
Hey, y'all.

28:54.139 --> 28:57.341
This is Alex, your daddy.

28:57.375 --> 29:01.412
Well, I mean, your husband
and your daddy.

29:02.514 --> 29:05.082
This feels kind of awkward, actually,

29:05.116 --> 29:08.719
talking like we all
don't know each other.

29:11.289 --> 29:16.293
But I guess it's... it has been a while.

29:17.696 --> 29:23.434
You know, you might not even
recognize me, little guy.

29:23.468 --> 29:28.038
So I should have called you
after the Donnager, I know.

29:28.073 --> 29:30.040
Well, I guess I'm doing it now, right?

29:30.075 --> 29:32.610
Better late than never.

29:32.644 --> 29:33.978
Sorry.

29:34.012 --> 29:36.313
I know you hate when I say that.

29:37.182 --> 29:39.283
[SIGHS] Look.

29:39.317 --> 29:41.852
<i>I just want to make sure y'all are safe,</i>

29:41.887 --> 29:44.154
<i>with everything that's been
going on right now.</i>

29:44.189 --> 29:46.457
<i>I don't think Earth would ever bomb Mars,</i>

29:46.491 --> 29:48.993
<i>but people have acting real crazy lately.</i>

29:49.027 --> 29:51.295
<i>So you pay extra special attention</i>

29:51.329 --> 29:53.697
<i>to those drills at school,
all right, cowboy?</i>

29:53.732 --> 29:55.065
<i>You listen to what the government</i>

29:55.100 --> 29:56.667
<i>and your mama tells you.</i>

29:56.701 --> 29:58.869
<i>It'll keep you safe.</i>

30:02.841 --> 30:04.911
I've been an awful husband...

30:06.111 --> 30:07.914
and a worse father.

30:09.848 --> 30:11.126
I know.

30:12.017 --> 30:13.651
<i>I'm just trying to...</i>

30:13.685 --> 30:16.587
<i>I'm just trying to do some good out here.</i>

30:16.621 --> 30:17.821
<i>And we have.</i>

30:17.856 --> 30:19.156
<i>I have.</i>

30:19.190 --> 30:20.891
<i>I think, uh...</i>

30:21.261 --> 30:25.195
I think this is what I've
always really wanted to do...

30:27.532 --> 30:29.900
More than I wanted to be there with you.

30:29.935 --> 30:32.903
<i>[TENDER MUSIC]</i>

30:32.938 --> 30:35.839
<i>♪ </i>

30:35.874 --> 30:39.043
I just could never
really tell you that...

30:41.613 --> 30:44.048
'Cause I don't think I knew myself.

30:48.119 --> 30:49.820
[SIGHS]

30:52.891 --> 30:54.258
But that doesn't mean

30:54.292 --> 30:58.128
that for one second I did not love you,

30:58.163 --> 30:59.758
both of you,

31:01.499 --> 31:03.233
very, very much.

31:13.979 --> 31:16.280
[BUTTONS TAPPING]

31:17.682 --> 31:20.250
<i>We are rigged for silent running.</i>

31:35.800 --> 31:38.769
<i>[TENSE MUSIC]</i>

31:38.803 --> 31:45.876
<i>♪ </i>

31:52.617 --> 31:55.285
[EXPLOSION BOOMS]

31:55.320 --> 31:58.288
<i>[DRAMATIC MUSIC]</i>

31:58.323 --> 32:02.926
<i>♪ </i>

32:02.961 --> 32:05.763
[PANTING]

32:05.797 --> 32:12.836
<i>♪ </i>

32:18.143 --> 32:20.477
[GRUNTS]

32:20.512 --> 32:21.745
[GRUNTS]

32:22.881 --> 32:24.782
[GRUNTING]

32:24.816 --> 32:27.151
[ELECTRONIC BEEPING]

32:27.185 --> 32:30.354
[GASPING AND YELLING]

32:34.225 --> 32:35.626
[YELLS]

32:35.660 --> 32:38.662
[ENGINES ROARING]

32:40.165 --> 32:43.500
[YELLING]

32:43.535 --> 32:46.036
[PANTING]

32:46.071 --> 32:49.206
[GRUNTING]

32:53.111 --> 32:56.346
[PANTING]

32:56.381 --> 32:59.149
- [CLICK]
- [GRUNTS]

32:59.184 --> 33:00.317
This plan sucks.

33:00.351 --> 33:02.386
I'm not gonna totally disagree.

33:02.420 --> 33:03.987
She isn't even a pilot.

33:04.022 --> 33:06.056
Well, I'd happily chauffeur,

33:06.091 --> 33:09.159
but you wouldn't want
to see the mess from this wound

33:09.194 --> 33:10.360
when we hit high six Gs.

33:10.395 --> 33:12.329
Even if you escape the missiles,

33:12.363 --> 33:14.264
the UN will fire on your drop ship

33:14.299 --> 33:15.833
when they come to mop up.

33:15.867 --> 33:19.240
The UN fire on an unarmed
ship bearing their own flag?

33:19.275 --> 33:21.772
They'll need to find out
if you're on board.

33:21.806 --> 33:23.240
So we'll be all right.

33:23.274 --> 33:30.547
<i>♪ </i>

33:44.062 --> 33:45.529
[BANG]

33:55.740 --> 34:02.779
<i>♪ </i>

34:22.311 --> 34:24.913
I've laid in a course that
avoids the high-traffic zones.

34:24.947 --> 34:26.947
It'll take us a bit longer, but...

34:26.983 --> 34:29.583
we'll get to Tycho quietly.

34:29.619 --> 34:31.186
I didn't give a fuck about your daughter.

34:31.219 --> 34:32.587
Jim!

34:32.621 --> 34:34.589
I used you to get us through Ganymede,

34:34.623 --> 34:35.690
and none of us would be breathing

34:35.725 --> 34:36.755
if you hadn't come.

34:36.789 --> 34:37.891
Look, you don't have to say that.

34:37.927 --> 34:39.793
We owe you some answers,

34:39.829 --> 34:41.963
so at least you know
we did everything we could

34:41.998 --> 34:43.732
to find her.

34:43.766 --> 34:46.301
The lab on Ganymede.

34:46.335 --> 34:47.735
That was a field lab.

34:47.770 --> 34:49.471
That's not where
they created those Hybrids...

34:49.505 --> 34:50.804
Can I just speak for a moment?

34:50.840 --> 34:52.706
When the Hybrid burned up in our drive,

34:52.742 --> 34:54.409
it timed exactly with that ship

34:54.443 --> 34:55.976
that got pulled apart over Venus.

34:56.012 --> 34:58.046
Now, we know the protomolecule
is connected,

34:58.080 --> 34:59.781
that it communicates with itself.

34:59.815 --> 35:04.252
And something else happened
at that same moment.

35:04.286 --> 35:07.088
A spike on lo,

35:07.123 --> 35:08.890
another "shout" from the protomolecule.

35:08.924 --> 35:10.892
And lo is still within range.

35:10.926 --> 35:12.894
Look, we've already decided...

35:12.928 --> 35:16.564
There's a decommissioned
Helium-3 refinery there...

35:16.599 --> 35:19.100
built by Jules-Pierre Mao.

35:23.372 --> 35:26.408
We've plotted
a safe, clean course for Tycho.

35:26.442 --> 35:27.609
Everything is there.

35:27.643 --> 35:29.511
We can go to Tycho... after lo.

35:29.545 --> 35:33.848
Jim, we're all devastated
about Prax's child,

35:33.883 --> 35:36.685
but sacrificing this crew
doesn't bring her back.

35:36.719 --> 35:38.620
Look past your anger towards me, please.

35:38.654 --> 35:40.321
This isn't about you.

35:40.356 --> 35:43.158
And I don't give a damn about
the protomolecule anymore.

35:43.192 --> 35:44.325
It's out there now.

35:44.360 --> 35:45.326
So be it.

35:45.361 --> 35:46.594
But we promised Prax

35:46.629 --> 35:48.129
we'd help him find his daughter,

35:48.164 --> 35:49.998
and we did every damn thing except that.

35:50.032 --> 35:51.299
We're all in agreement.

35:51.333 --> 35:53.668
Tycho is the only way we survive.

35:53.703 --> 35:56.638
I assure you,
Fred Johnson will help us...

35:56.672 --> 35:58.056
Io.

35:58.974 --> 36:00.608
- Fuck it, I'm in.
- Amos...

36:00.643 --> 36:02.844
Me too.

36:02.878 --> 36:04.746
I'll go set a course.

36:10.720 --> 36:12.253
[GASPS]

36:20.663 --> 36:22.964
<i>...which threatens
to throw the Inner Planets</i>

36:22.998 --> 36:25.700
<i>into a state of all-out war...</i>

36:25.735 --> 36:29.504
More ships, more war, more death.

36:29.538 --> 36:31.639
You and Dawes want to join that party?

36:31.674 --> 36:34.309
The idea is to prevent exactly that.

36:34.343 --> 36:36.311
Ah, yes, a "deterrent."

36:36.345 --> 36:39.714
But everything becomes a weapon, Freddy.

36:39.749 --> 36:41.015
Didn't you teach me that?

36:41.050 --> 36:43.384
Sometimes you make your move.

36:43.419 --> 36:44.686
It's the Belt's moment,

36:44.720 --> 36:46.321
and we didn't get to choose it.

36:46.355 --> 36:49.324
You have your big ideas.

36:49.358 --> 36:50.859
And I get shot.

36:52.528 --> 36:53.762
You know why I stayed with you

36:53.796 --> 36:55.363
after Dawes dragged you
out of the gutter,

36:55.397 --> 36:58.833
after I convinced him
not to put you down like a dog?

36:58.868 --> 37:00.168
To keep an eye on me.

37:00.202 --> 37:01.703
Dawes wasn't convinced of my loyalty.

37:01.737 --> 37:03.671
Dawes wanted me back on Ceres,

37:03.706 --> 37:06.166
and I wanted to get away.

37:06.809 --> 37:09.210
No future down his road.

37:10.079 --> 37:12.080
I saw something different in you.

37:12.114 --> 37:14.883
I chose you.

37:16.752 --> 37:19.854
Well, then... I'm glad you did.

37:19.889 --> 37:22.991
And we built Tycho together.

37:24.560 --> 37:26.261
A way forward for the Belt.

37:26.295 --> 37:29.731
Now that blue siren has got you dreaming

37:29.765 --> 37:32.233
about bigger things, huh?

37:32.268 --> 37:33.234
When I'm pissed off,

37:33.269 --> 37:34.869
you normally have the good sense

37:34.904 --> 37:36.738
to stay the hell away
for a couple of days,

37:36.772 --> 37:39.307
and it's been two hours.

37:39.341 --> 37:40.642
So what is it you want?

37:40.676 --> 37:43.311
[ROCK MUSIC PLAYING]

37:43.345 --> 37:49.250
♪

37:49.285 --> 37:51.486
I need you to lead a salvage mission.

37:51.520 --> 37:53.054
Bring back the Nauvoo.

37:54.290 --> 37:56.724
You gonna make nice with the Mormons?

37:56.759 --> 37:58.159
No, why would you?

37:58.194 --> 38:00.495
We're gonna retrofit
the ship for the Belt,

38:00.529 --> 38:04.399
because soon we're not
gonna be a bunch of tribes.

38:04.433 --> 38:06.067
We're gonna be a nation.

38:06.101 --> 38:08.069
Sounds a little like
you want me out of the way.

38:08.103 --> 38:10.171
No, it's exactly what I'm saying it is.

38:10.206 --> 38:11.806
Yeah, the doctor's been telling me

38:11.841 --> 38:14.309
I need to take a vacation to heal up.

38:14.343 --> 38:16.678
I can't do this without you.

38:16.712 --> 38:18.146
Once Earth and Mars get done

38:18.180 --> 38:20.248
beating each other back to the Stone Age,

38:20.282 --> 38:22.483
they're gonna need the Belt
more than ever.

38:22.518 --> 38:23.751
We need to be ready.

38:23.786 --> 38:25.453
A cathedral converted into a warship,

38:25.487 --> 38:30.091
sounds like the heart
of a great and lasting nation.

38:31.327 --> 38:32.919
I need you.

38:33.629 --> 38:35.096
Will you go?

38:37.833 --> 38:40.435
Can I finish my drink first?

38:40.469 --> 38:43.438
<i>[DRAMATIC MUSIC]</i>

38:43.472 --> 38:51.012
<i>♪ </i>

38:51.046 --> 38:52.180
Less than five minutes.

38:52.214 --> 38:54.782
Easy, cowboy, plenty of time.

38:54.817 --> 38:56.885
Ice water in my veins under pressure.

38:56.919 --> 38:59.654
That's why you hired me, right?

38:59.688 --> 39:00.855
It's gonna be okay.

39:00.890 --> 39:02.257
Okay?

39:04.360 --> 39:07.195
Don't forget your antibiotics.

39:10.532 --> 39:12.000
I won't.

39:18.540 --> 39:19.807
Good job, Marine.

39:19.842 --> 39:21.509
Same to you, spy.

39:28.918 --> 39:33.321
<i>♪ </i>

39:33.355 --> 39:35.189
[PANEL CLANGS]

39:39.528 --> 39:41.062
Now we're anonymous.

39:41.096 --> 39:42.697
I need to stow my suit.

39:42.731 --> 39:44.198
Take off all that tinsel.

39:44.233 --> 39:45.600
Is this really the time
for fashion advice?

39:45.634 --> 39:47.936
At six Gs, that junk
will tear your head off.

39:47.970 --> 39:49.370
You decide.

39:51.740 --> 39:57.512
<i>♪ </i>

39:57.546 --> 39:59.747
[GROANING]

39:59.782 --> 40:01.549
Go, go, go, go!

40:06.889 --> 40:08.856
[ELECTRONIC BEEPING]

40:08.891 --> 40:16.164
<i>♪ </i>

40:30.245 --> 40:31.980
Just gonna tea-kettle nice and easy

40:32.014 --> 40:33.748
out into the big empty.

40:33.782 --> 40:35.049
And then what happens?

40:35.084 --> 40:37.085
I'm interested to find that out myself.

40:42.024 --> 40:43.624
Powering up.

40:43.659 --> 40:51.099
<i>♪ </i>

41:09.518 --> 41:12.086
[MISSILES WHOOSHING]

41:12.121 --> 41:19.327
<i>♪ </i>

41:27.069 --> 41:28.603
I'm no expert,

41:28.637 --> 41:31.272
but shouldn't we get
the hell away from that yacht?

41:31.306 --> 41:33.107
Not too soon, or one of those
missiles might see us

41:33.142 --> 41:34.175
and lock on our drive.

41:34.209 --> 41:35.943
Did Cotyar get out?

41:35.978 --> 41:38.413
I'm sure he did. Now quiet.

41:40.749 --> 41:42.984
<i>Prepare for clamp release.</i>

41:46.688 --> 41:49.624
<i>♪ </i>

41:49.658 --> 41:51.459
Shall we shove off now, please?

41:51.493 --> 41:53.461
Sit still, you're gonna need it.

41:55.064 --> 41:56.898
Oh, oh!

41:56.932 --> 41:58.800
Get me off this ship!

41:58.834 --> 42:00.001
Hitch your tits and pucker up.

42:00.035 --> 42:01.469
It's time to peel the paint.

42:01.503 --> 42:02.703
Shit!

42:05.074 --> 42:06.674
[ENGINE ROARING]

42:08.177 --> 42:12.146
[EXPLOSIONS BOOMING]

42:14.116 --> 42:18.086
[WHIRRING AND WHOOSHING]

42:18.120 --> 42:19.887
Brace for impact.

42:19.922 --> 42:23.658
[METAL WHOOSHING AND CLANGING]

42:26.728 --> 42:28.496
[GRUNTING]

42:28.530 --> 42:34.035
<i>♪ </i>

42:34.037 --> 43:38.166
(OMINOUS TONES)

